parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupancy Mat (OC3) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupancy mat can cause the airbag and seatbelt to malfunction, leading to a risk of bodily harm or death to passengers in the event of a collision.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on in dashboard
failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts to repair the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in fixing the safety issue, putting drivers and passengers at risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Pump and Electric Thermostat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the water pump and electric thermostat can cause engine overheating, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
Engine shut-off without warning can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
and the driver is left stranded.
